OL,3,CNew terrorism offence recommended in
OL,4,Cwake of Southport attack
OL,6,FHe referenced the case of Nicholas
OL,7,FProsper, 19, who murdered his mother
OL,8,Fand two siblings and was on his was to
OL,9,Fcarry out a mass shooting at his old
OL,10,Fprimary school when he was stopped by
OL,11,Fpolice.
OL,13,FA loaded shotgun was found hidden in
OL,14,Fbushes nearby, with a bag of more than
OL,15,F30 cartridges, when officers spotted
OL,16,Fhim in Bramingham Road, Luton.
OL,18,FThere is not a specific offence that
OL,19,Fhe could be charged with for planning
OL,20,Fthe school shooting because his plot
OL,21,Fwould not be defined as terrorism.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/14
