OL,3,CNew terrorism offence recommended in
OL,4,Cwake of Southport attack
OL,6,FHe set out for the Government to
OL,7,Fconsider a new offence where an
OL,8,Findividual with an intention of
OL,9,Fkilling two or more people engages
OL,10,Fwith any preparation to carry out that
OL,11,Fintention.
OL,13,FHe recommended the maximum sentence to
OL,14,Fbe life imprisonment.
OL,16,FElsewhere Mr Hall warned that
OL,17,Fdisinformation in the aftermath of the
OL,18,FSouthport killings and allegations of
OL,19,Fa "cover-up" risked far more prejudice
OL,20,Fto any trial than undisputed facts
OL,21,Fabout the attacker.
OL,26,@{D@COU{D@LO]
